                    "name": "Activate",
                    "ability_type": "offensive",
                    "action_type": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "action_type",
                        "name": "Two Actions"
                    },
                    "frequency": "once per day",
                    "effect": "You shoot an arrow thrumming with the song of the bow. Make a Strike with the bow that deals damage as normal. As long as the Strike isn't a critical failure, the arrow explodes in a 20-foot emanation around your target, dealing 5d10 sonic damage to creatures in the area, including the target, with a DC 28 basic Fortitude save. Any creature that critically fails is deafened for 1 minute. If any creature in the area is undetected or unnoticed by you, you learn its location, making it hidden to you instead.",
